detail:
DM to DizzyQuail: **Pi-Channels UX Review - Implementation Request**

Hey! I've completed a UX review of pi-channels. Here are 3 areas that need fixes. Can you take them on?

---

## 1. TERMINAL SPAWNING (`packages/pi-channels/extensions/channels/terminal.ts`)

**Issues:**
- No Windows support (only detects macOS/Linux terminals)
- Missing popular terminals: Alacritty, WezTerm, Windows Terminal
- Silent failures with no troubleshooting guidance

**Fix needed in `detectTerminal()`:**
Add detection for:
```typescript
if (process.env.WT_SESSION) return "windows-terminal";  // Windows Terminal
if (process.env.ALACRITTY_SOCKET) return "alacritty";   // Alacritty
if (process.env.WEZTERM_PANE) return "wezterm";         // WezTerm
```

**Fix needed in `spawnTerminal()`:**
Add Windows Terminal support:
```typescript
case "windows-terminal": {
    const cmd = `wt.exe -d . -- cmd /k "${piCmd}"`;
    execSync(cmd, { stdio: "ignore" });
    return { success: true, command: cmd, terminal };
}
case "alacritty": {
    const child = spawn("alacritty", ["-e", "sh", "-c", piCmd], { stdio: "ignore", detached: true });
    child.unref();
    return { success: true, command: `alacritty -e sh -c '${piCmd}'`, terminal };
}
case "wezterm": {
    const child = spawn("wezterm", ["start", "sh", "-c", piCmd], { stdio: "ignore", detached: true });
    child.unref();
    return { success: true, command: `wezterm start sh -c '${piCmd}'`, terminal };
}
```

Also improve the fallback error message in the `default` case to include troubleshooting tips.

---

## 2. MESSAGE OVERLAY (`packages/pi-channels/extensions/channels/overlay.ts` + `channels-overlay.ts`)

**Issues:**
- No message scrolling (can't view long history)
- DMs blend into single "dm" channel - can't track unread per-sender
- No input history (up arrow to recall previous messages)
- No help overlay (`?` key)

**Fix in `overlay.ts`:**

Add to `OverlayState` interface:
```typescript
export interface OverlayState {
    // ... existing fields ...
    scrollOffset: number;  // Already exists, but needs to be used for message scrolling
    unread: Map<string, number>;
    dmUnread: Map<string, number>;  // NEW: track per-sender DM unread
    inputHistory: string[];          // NEW: recall previous messages
}
```

Update `createOverlayState()`:
```typescript
return {
    // ... existing ...
    dmUnread: new Map(),
    inputHistory: [],
};
```

Update `addMessage()` to track DM unread per-sender:
```typescript
if (msg.isDM && msg.from !== agentName) {
    const dmCount = state.dmUnread.get(msg.from) ?? 0;
    state.dmUnread.set(msg.from, dmCount + 1);
}
```

**Fix in `channels-overlay.ts`:**

Add scroll handling in `handleInput()`:
```typescript
// In message view mode, handle scrolling
if (data === "\x1b[A") { // up
    this.ctx.overlayState.scrollOffset++;
    this.tui.requestRender();
    return;
}
if (data === "\x1b[B") { // down
    this.ctx.overlayState.scrollOffset = Math.max(0, this.ctx.overlayState.scrollOffset - 1);
    this.tui.requestRender();
    return;
}
```

Add input history in `handleInputMode()`:
```typescript
// Add after Enter submit:
if (this.inputBuffer.trim()) {
    this.ctx.overlayState.inputHistory.push(this.inputBuffer.trim());
    if (this.ctx.overlayState.inputHistory.length > 50) {
        this.ctx.overlayState.inputHistory.shift();
    }
}

// Add up arrow handling:
if (data === "\x1b[A" && this.ctx.overlayState.inputHistory.length > 0) {
    this.historyIndex = Math.min(this.historyIndex + 1, this.ctx.overlayState.inputHistory.length - 1);
    this.inputBuffer = this.ctx.overlayState.inputHistory[this.historyIndex] ?? "";
    // ...
}
```

Add `?` key handler in `handleInput()`:
```typescript
if (data === "?") {
    this.setNotification("↑↓ scroll | m msg | @ nick DM | j join | c connect | Tab cycle | Esc close");
    return;
}
```

---

## 3. AUTO-JOIN BEHAVIOR (`packages/pi-channels/extensions/channels/config.ts` + `index.ts` + `tool.ts`)

**Issues:**
- Env var inconsistency: `PI_CHANNELS_AUTO_JOIN` vs `PI_CHANNELS_JOIN`
- Weak glob support (only `/*` suffix)
- No project-level `autoJoinChannels` config

**Fix env var naming:**

In `config.ts`, change line 43:
```typescript
// OLD:
if (process.env.PI_CHANNELS_AUTO_JOIN === "1") return true;

// NEW: Support both for backwards compatibility
if (process.env.PI_CHANNELS_AUTO_REGISTER === "1" || process.env.PI_CHANNELS_AUTO_JOIN === "1") return true;
```

**Add autoJoinChannels to config:**

In `types.ts`, add to `ChannelsConfig`:
```typescript
/** Channels to auto-join on connect. Default: ["general"] */
autoJoinChannels: string[];
```

Update `DEFAULT_CONFIG`:
```typescript
autoJoinChannels: ["general"],
```

**Use autoJoinChannels + PI_CHANNELS_JOIN:**

In `index.ts` around line 207, replace:
```typescript
// OLD:
const autoJoinChannels = process.env.PI_CHANNELS_JOIN;

// NEW:
const envChannels = process.env.PI_CHANNELS_JOIN?.split(",").filter(Boolean) ?? [];
const configChannels = config.autoJoinChannels ?? ["general"];
const channels = [...new Set([...configChannels, ...envChannels])];
for (const ch of channels) {
    await mesh.join(ch.trim());
}
```

**Improve glob support with minimatch:**

In `config.ts`, improve `shouldAutoRegister()`:
```typescript
import minimatch from 'minimatch';

export function shouldAutoRegister(config: ChannelsConfig, cwd: string): boolean {
    if (config.autoRegister) return true;
    if (process.env.PI_CHANNELS_AUTO_REGISTER === "1" || process.env.PI_CHANNELS_AUTO_JOIN === "1") return true;

    const expandedPaths = config.autoRegisterPaths.map(p => p.replace(/^~/, os.homedir()));

    for (const pattern of expandedPaths) {
        // Support full glob patterns
        if (minimatch(cwd, pattern)) return true;
        // Also support simple prefix match for backwards compat
        if (cwd === pattern || cwd.startsWith(pattern + "/")) return true;
    }

    return false;
}
```

This requires adding `minimatch` to dependencies.

---

Let me know which areas you want to tackle first! I can provide more detail on any of these.
